'''螃蟹心理'''（{{lang-en|'''Crab Mentality'''}}），通常也被稱作'''桶子裡的螃蟹'''，形容西方俚語「如果我沒有，你也不可以有」的[[心理|心理]]，此比喻參照在一個充滿[[螃蟹|螃蟹]]的桶子，雖然牠們能輕易從桶子裡逃出，然而在下面的螃蟹往往會互相抓住來防止其他螃蟹逃出，確保牠們遭到同一樣的下場<ref>{{cite web |url=http://opinion.inquirer.net/inquireropinion/letterstotheeditor/view/20100514-270015/Crab-mentality |title=Crab mentality – INQUIRER.net, Philippine News for Filipinos |publisher=Opinion.inquirer.net |date=2010-05-14 |accessdate=2012-05-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925140458/http://opinion.inquirer.net/inquireropinion/letterstotheeditor/view/20100514-270015/Crab-mentality |archivedate=2013-09-25 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/cagayan-de-oro/opinion/2012/05/03/dureza-naughty-pnoy-219434 |title=Dureza: The naughty PNoy |publisher=Sun.Star |date=2012-05-03 |accessdate=2012-05-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130823052058/http://www.sunstar.com.ph/cagayan-de-oro/opinion/2012/05/03/dureza-naughty-pnoy-219434 |archivedate=2013-08-23 }}</ref>。這比喻是比喻[[人類|人類]]的行為當中，例如小組成員會嘗試拉倒做到超越他自己的其他成員(否定或削弱其重要性)，但只是出於[[嫉妒|嫉妒]]，陰險或競爭的心理。但這不能展現出大部分螃蟹的心理，因為牠們只是想逃出桶子而沒有任何對成敗的[[知識|知識]]和理解。

==影響==
螃蟹心理亦被與眼光短淺，非建設性的想法廣泛關聯而不是統一，長期，建設性的心態<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110710185025/http://emanila.com/philippines/2010/01/19/crab-mentality-is-universal/ Crab Mentality Is Universal](January 19, 2010. Part 7 of the "In Defense of the Filipino" series.), [http://emanila.co http://emanila.com]. (archived from [http://emanila.com/philippines/2010/01/19/crab-mentality-is-universal/ the original] {{Wayback|url=http://emanila.com/philippines/2010/01/19/crab-mentality-is-universal/ |date=20110710185025 }} on 2011-07-10)</ref>。2015年[[新西蘭|新西蘭]]對此的研究指出，大部分考生有超過18%的平均分的進步由於他們避免讓別人看見其上次考試的排名。<ref name="Spacey">[http://www.srl.to/u5e2dNha Spacey, S. 2015. Crab Mentality, Cyberbullying and "Name and Shame" Rankings. In Press, Waikato University, New Zealand]. Retrieved on April 19th, 2015.</ref>
但根據前後關係，此[[戰術|戰術]]亦被認為是不受歡迎的，並認為是出於妒忌心<ref>{{cite web |url=http://constitution.org/col/logical_fallacies.htm |title=Logical Fallacies |publisher=Constitution Society |date=2012-10-19 |accessdate=2012-10-29 |archive-date=2020-06-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200616225204/https://constitution.org/col/logical_fallacies.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。然而即使人们知道其行為對此不利，但他們亦會因此而經常因資源的缺乏引起恆久的[[戰爭|戰爭]]。<ref>{{cite news|last=Sarangi|first=Sudipta|title=Capturing Indian ‘crab’ behaviour|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/opinion/capturing-indian-crab-behaviour/article4570414.ece|accessdate=6 May 2014|newspaper=The Hindu - Business Line|archive-date=2014-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140506085955/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/opinion/capturing-indian-crab-behaviour/article4570414.ece|dead-url=no}}</ref>

